\lettrine[lines=4]{\color{black!45}M}{atter} is everywhere around you, from the water you drink to the air you inhale. The matter is made of elements and elements are made of atoms. In the world, we can also find light, that somehow at first sight seems different than matter. Light is warm and it has color. This chapter covers the structure of the atoms, with a focus on the structure of the many electrons that atoms are made of. It also focuses on light and the interaction of light with matter. You will be able to understand differences in electronic configuration.